					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There is really short period when the VRAM access is possible - ~2700t, and 513+ are needed to do sprite DMA. So, if you need to put many values into VRAM, you have to write this part in assembly. Even further, you should prepare the values before getting into NMI, and use unrolled loops. If you have enough RAM, you can even generate a pusher subroutine, like sequence of 'lda #nn sta PPU_DATA', this way you'll get 6t/byte for sequental write and will be able to push a sequence of ~350 bytes. Much less for random writes, like 100 bytes.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

