					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">For this on-the-fly code, you can use X and Y for commonly used values. Do the updates to each 256-byte page of VRAM together and then X can hold $20 for the first few, then $21, etc., and Y whatever the most common value is. So you get code like<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">ldx #$20<br />ldy #$00<br />stx $2006<br />lda #$08<br />sta $2006<br />sty $2007<br />stx $2006<br />lda #$25<br />sta $2006<br />lda #$10<br />sta $2007<br />stx $2006</div></div>

