					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I thought I should mention that I've settled on a hybrid NMI approach - vram updates and music in the VMI, with a &quot;callback&quot; in the NMI to do whatever custom stuff needs doing, and controller polling and game logic in the main thread.  Trying to poll controllers in the NMI was a disaster, not sure why.  Anyway I think splitting the threads is a good idea in general for framerate and CPU control.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />sonder</div>
